-4fd5-82a1-5168df37b295.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture of the active sessions. Let me analyze the sessions excluding the cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e (this cron session):\n\nActive sessions (status = running, excluding this cron session):\n1. `main` - running, started ~13:45:11 UTC, webchat heartbeat\n2. `cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` - running, started ~09:11:26 UTC (5p QLHV progress), ~4h 33m\n\n\n3. `cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` - running, started ~07:25:01 UTC (5p DTLX progress), ~6h 19m\n4. `telegram:direct:6053576134` - done (ended ~12:02:38 UTC)\n5. `telegram:group:-5163901258` - running, started ~11:56:48 UTC, ~1h 47m\n6. `cron:b653a6c0` - still gathering session details\n\n, but appears to have stopped at ~11:57:33 UTC\n\nNow I'm calculating the actual durations from the timestamps. The main session has been running for about 13 minutes, the QLHV progress cron for roughly 4.5 hours, and the DTLX progress cron for around 6 hours. The QLHV group Telegram session has been active for about 1 hour and 47 minutes.\n\nLooking at the overall picture, there are 5 active sessions currently running, and I should note that the cron:b653a6c0 session appears to be a zombie from a previous cycle since its endedAt timestamp predates its updatedAt. The Agent Status to Lead cron also just sent a report to Lead's Telegram recently, which is a recent development.\n\nNow I'm calculating the duration for each running session and preparing the report to send to Lead's Telegram. I'll format it with the current timestamp and list out each session with its status, task, and runtime.\n\nGenerating markdown table..."},{"type":"text","text":"I can see there are 5 other active sessions besides this cron session. Let me compile and send the report.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0y35myuosqoq_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orche