to be stuck or outdated, and I need to flag these failed agents as requiring attention. I've identified three failed subagent sessions and one killed agent, but since these failures occurred before the last heartbeat snapshot at 13:36 UTC, they're not new changes. However, looking at the recent activity more carefully, I'm noticing something happened around 13:44 UTC when the Agent Status cron sent a report to Lead's Telegram, though this was just a notification rather than a session state change. Let me check what other sessions are currently active to get a fuller picture. So there are 36 sessions total in the list, but most are already terminated. Let me identify which ones are actually still running based on the status fieldвҖ”I'm seeing several with \"running\" status that need to be accounted for in the current heartbeat check. Looking at the timestamp more carefully, I'm realizing the \"running\" status on that Telegram session is actually staleвҖ”the endedAt timestamp of 1776163783190 converts to 12:03 UTC, which means it's been done for almost two hours. So the actual active sessions I need to track are just the three cron jobs and the main session, with that Telegram group session being a false positive in the list. Everything's stable across all sessions with no changes detected, so I'm staying silent on this.","thinkingSignature":"ec58a6ea258ad8bd794ab3ae4d32995474d01d9a84dd4c582c62c604217bc091"},{"type":"text","text":"All sessions stable. Comparing against 13:36 UTC baseline:\n\n- вң… `cron:ed2d0b5d` вҖ” still running (updated 13:54 UTC)\n- вң… `cron:6f3323ef` вҖ” still running (updated 13:51 UTC)\n- вң… `cron:e7885813` вҖ” still running (updated 13:45 UTC)\n- вң… `main` вҖ” done (since 13:06 UTC)\n- вң… `telegram:group:-5163901258` вҖ” done (since 13:00 UTC)\n- вң… Pre-existing zombies unchanged\n\nNo changes detected. Silent exit."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":966,"output":876,"cacheRe